- VSCode Version: Code - Insiders 1.10.0-insider (1c1f82e9722d2fafdbebb7524ac2cc465aafdfb4, 2017-02-09T11:45:48.163Z)
- OS Version: Windows_NT ia32 10.0.14986

Assuming you have an extension like this that provides a code action for every range in the document (same code as in #19562):

```ts
'use strict';
import * as vscode from 'vscode';

export function activate(context: vscode.ExtensionContext) {
    vscode.languages.registerCodeActionsProvider('haxe', {
        provideCodeActions(doc, range, message) {
            return [{
                title: doc.getText(range),
                command: ""
            }];
        }
    });
}
```

The quick fix menu pops up automatically whenever I open a file (in seemingly random places, but always with the first word in the document):

![](http://i.imgur.com/9DFiguL.gif)

Note that this already happened in the previous Insider's build before @jrieken's fix for #19562 (definitely a regression compared to 1.9.x however).

I would like to be able to achieve the following scenario using URL handlers for VS Code, giving a quick start for any new developers interested in developing using my extension. This issue is about step 2:

//1. Install VS Code -  https://code.visualstudio.com/download
**2. Clone a git hub repository with sample source code -  vscode://gitclone/https/github.com/Microsoft/AL/**
//3. Install extension - vscode://extension/microsoft.al

Step 3 seems to be supported but doesn't work - see #20289
